# AGENT CONTEXT: This directory holds all infrastructure-as-code for the monorepo.
#
# Infrastructure lives alongside app and package code so that:
#   - A single PR can include both application changes and infra changes
#   - Infra versioning is tied to the same git history as the code it serves
#   - No separate infra repo context-switch is needed (Company of One efficiency)
#
# ANTICIPATED STRUCTURE (populated by CMP-12):
#   infra/
#     docker/
#       docker-compose.yml        (local dev environment)
#       docker-compose.prod.yml   (production overrides)
#     k8s/                        (if/when Kubernetes is adopted)
#     terraform/                  (if/when cloud IaC is needed)
#     scripts/                    (deployment and utility shell scripts)
#
# IMPORTANT: Terraform state files (.tfstate) are in .gitignore.
# Never commit state files — they can contain secrets and are environment-specific.
# Use remote state (S3, Terraform Cloud) for any real environments.
#
# CMP-12 will populate this directory with Docker Compose configuration.
# This .gitkeep file can be deleted once any real content is committed here.
